 v0.58ŕ    It is time for 32bit                            June 09th, 1998

           Ok, I was some lazy the past month ( My new program 'Girlfriend'
           does not like my old good 'Coding 1.0' so there was some
           debugging to come arround :) but now I have finished something
           you will love !

           STIGMA proudly presents:
                                    THE 32bit MIXER !

           * the old 16 bit mixer is now the fast mixer and can handle
             about 32 channels without clipping even on slower PCs.
             Now a mixer with 32bit calculation width is developed and
             using 24 bits per sample. The samples are extended in the
             interpolation and volume routines just like in the 16bit mixer.
             So every channel has a dynamic of 166 dB !!!!!!!!!!!!!
             (the 16bit mixer has dynamic of 72 dB which is also good enough
             for good old 8 bit cards :)
             And all possible channels together have 192 dB dynamic range
             (a CD has 96 dB) but this must then downcalculated to fit in
             the 16bit, 96 dB output stream of the soundcards. :<
             But with this mixer there are nearly no round errors possible
             anymore and therefor is output 'finer and cleaner' which is real
             noticeable !
                               !!  I LOVE QUALITY  !!
             Additionaly are now up to 256 channels available for output !
             (IT here we come!) :->

           + full realtime interpolation in 1st grade is available now.
             There should be all click-bugs removed (hopefully)
           - but soft clipping is not implemented yet. The algorithm is much
             more complex for the 32bit mixer :(
           # strange bug in interrupt handler causes an exeption under
             Windows 95. It seems it only occurs if the machine is faster
             than a Pentium 133 :(
             So I added some extra stuff to avoid this mystery error.
             Now it should work fine ! (at my P200 it works now !)

