 v0.61ŕ    WAV strikes back !                              July 26th, 1998

           + WAV can now be played at any frequency the soundcard can take.
             This will be realised by a interpolation/resampling routine
             in realtime during playback.

           # I made a bad mistake in the routine which extend the orginal
             protracker note/periode table. So there could be periodes not
             recognized and therefor could no note found for that periode.
             Very high notes going over the amiga limit should now played
             correct.
             By the way, I have made the periode to note converter a bit
             more flexible :)

           # I found a bug in the interpolation mixer !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
             Well, indeed it is an (possible) overrun in a 32bit integer
             which can cause crackles and clicks and so I tried my first
             time the new 64bit integer Watcom supplies since 11.0 !
             Curiosly I found it during my implemention of the WAV resampler
             for that I copied some interpolation routines from the mixer
             and I wondered why they did not work all the time :)
             Now there are lesser clicks but I'm sure there are some errors
             elsewhere...

---************************************************************************---

 v0.62ŕ    Soft clipping goes 32bit                   September 01th, 1998

           Ok, this will be a bigger release with more fixes and extensions
           than usually :)

           # A bug in the S3M interpreter causes strange high notes when
             'amiga limit' flag was set in the S3M. Now this should be fixed
             quite fine and all S3Ms saved with this flag should be now
             played as in ST3.2
           + The fast volumeslides (mainly for oldold S3Ms) are now
             implemented so the old "Unreal" S3Ms sound a bit better :)

           # A bug in the MOD instrument reader causes all samples with a
             loop start set higher than zero to be treated as a looped sample
             which can cause a hang up if the loop length is set to zero :-P
             And if not is could produce strange sample loops... ups, fixed !

           # curiously by the last cleanup I made the same bug in the
             S3M and MOD interpreter even they are absolutly different :)
             All Retrig commands did not work, because I made a mistake in
             the 'last effect' remember routine in which every time a
             allowed effect was recognized the 'last effect' holder was
             overwritten with that new one. Probably there were more effects
             which did not work property due to this bug, but I hope they do
             fine now.

           + broken WAVs which are not as long as the header says are now
             played correct. This could happen if you dump an audio track
             from CD and abort it or the dump program lost the last bytes :(
             (I hate those shitty programs !)

           + loop-click removal in the interpolation mixer is perfect
             now ! This method is mathematical correct, it's not like
             >If you don't hear it, it is good enough!<
             YEAH ! I finally found the damn math bug in the Imixer :-D

           + Soft clipping is now also available for the 32bit mixer !
             This was a real hard task but now this should be fine :)
             (In 16bit mixer this was a table with 65536 entries, but for
             32 bit I would need 4 Gig !!!! No good idea I think !!!!!)
             Now you can play those overleveled modules and the clipping
             will be much better with lesser noise !

         ! I'm working in the moment on a comercial project so my time is
           now a bit more limited than usually ;)
           But I will work on the FX and give new releases every month !

