                        - What we are working on -

 coming soon...

           + alpha routines of sample-precalculation!
             This means recalculating a whole sample with a higher rate
             (and bitwidth) via a complex interpolation algorithm,
             a true spline algorithm which is almost similiar to a cubical
             interpolation but with one difference: Here the first derivative
             is smooth and the second is continuous with this type of
             interpolation.
             With a normal cubic interpolation the first derivative is
             continuous and the second undefined. So this needs a really
             heavy calculation and it could take some seconds to finish
             if it is activated and the samples will take up much more memory,
             but the quality is a lot better with less aliasing even if
             playing without interpolation.
             I searched months to find a good solution for a first class
             interpolation algorithm and I needed 2 weeks to fix it to my
             needs, so I am real proud of it and I hope you appreciate it!

           ! The command line routines are completly new and quite a bit more
             clear :)

           ! New anti-click-routines for with I have to make serious changes
             to the actuall mixer so that can cause new problems...

           + new system of configuration files
             The old .INI file is now divided in two separate files:
             The .CFG file takes all the low level system stuff like
             hardware settings for different soundcards and devices
             and timings for predefined filters (in the future).
             The .INI file includes appearance and user settings as
             well as the choosen sounddevice and desktop colors.

           + I try my first sound effects for a 'different' output.
             This includes 'stereo base extension' and other things...

           ! I start to make my familiar with the XM format. It's only
             a question of time when I will start to implement it!

           ! A very very poor MP3 player is in development now :(


 coming sometime...

